<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1269">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 211.42H78/7</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Spring
                                Rice</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: In an official note
                            dated to-day I am making application to the United States Government on
                            behalf of the Government of Canada for the extradition of Vernil Horne
                            who is accused of having attempted to destroy the Vanceboro Bridge in
                            the Province of New Brunswick. The danger which such acts may entail for
                            innocent travellers appears to me to point strongly to the advisability
                            of taking special precautions and I would suggest for your consideration
                            that guards should be placed on the American side of all international
                            bridges between Canada and the United States with a view to preventing
                            any similar outrages.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>